===Etymology===
French ''[[zeste]]''. Of unknown origin. The original meaning is 2. Meaning 1. ("enthusiasm") is metaphorical; confer ''[[to give a zest to]]'', meaning "to add piquancy to", which can be done with a zest (meaning 2.).
